{
  "texts": [
    "By categorizing needs as either direct or latent, this method aims to identify subliminal expectations, thereby facilitating information extraction from text-a crucial aspect of requirements engineering.",
    "Figure 1 illustrates the development process of ReqGPT.",
    "First, 120 requirements lists for products from the consumer goods sector were automatically created employing few-shot prompting with GPT-4 using a requirements list structure extracted from Hubka et al. (1988).",
    "Precisely 107 of these lists satisfied all necessary criteria according to ISO 29148 (2018), providing a robust dataset for the subsequent training.",
    "The training was performed on the base model of Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.2 over nine epochs, ensuring comprehensive data integration and processing efficiency."
  ]
}